Things to try:
--quiet or -q

$ ansible-playbook myplaybook.yml > ansible.log 2> >(grep -vE '^(.*\[[0-9]+\]: )?ERROR.*$' > /dev/null)

The grep -vE '^(.*\[[0-9]+\]: )?ERROR.*$' command matches lines that do not contain an error message generated by Ansible itself. 
The -v option tells grep to invert the match, so it only outputs lines that do not match the pattern. 
The regular expression ^(.*\[[0-9]+\]: )?ERROR.*$ matches lines that start with an optional string in the form some_text[1]: , followed by the string ERROR.

ansible-playbook myplaybook.yml | tee output.log




